" His Honour then considered all the alleged incidents and found that the applicant had " not established any basis for the grant of relief under the Human Rights and Equal Opportunities Commission Act" sic;
" Human Rights and Equal Opportunity Act" . The application was dismissed in relation to all respondents. The applicant has appealed against that decision but on 4 April 2007 was ordered by Justice Flick to provide security for costs in respect of all respondents Lawrance v Commonwealth [2008] FCA 417. (See Affidavit of Mee (supra) at paragraph 14). The Court notes that the conduct complained of in SYG 2015 of 2006 was substantially the same as in matters SYG 2109 of 2006 and 
SYG 655 of 2007. The actual costs expended by the State of NSW were in excess of $38,000. The applicant appealed and sought a stay of costs. On 4 April 2008 Justice Flick dismissed the application for a stay of the order for costs and ordered security of costs for all respondents Lawrance v Commonwealth [2008] FCA 417 (see Affidavit of Mee, paragraph 14). At paragraph 12 Justice Flick stated: "... Second, the order as made by the Federal Magistrate is an order that would normally be expected to be made given the given dismissal by the Court of her application" Security of costs for $10,000 was ordered for the first and third to thirteenth respondents (which include the Commonwealth, DFaCSIA, CRS and AGS); security for costs of $12,000 was ordered for the second respondent (the State of NSW). In the Affidavit of Mee at paragraph 28, she states the State of NSW has incurred costs of $113,000 in responding to the applications by the applicant, and at paragraph 29 that the Guardianship Tribunal's costs exceed $37,000.
